"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124237","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-05-08","<p>Through ‘Childhood obesity: a plan for action, Chapter 2’, we are delivering a Trailblazer Programme in partnership with the Local Government Association and Public Health England, working with local authorities to address childhood obesity at local level.</p><p>The programme has a strong focus on inequalities and ethnic disparities in childhood obesity and in the next phase that begins this spring, the Trailblazer Programme will support five local authorities with £100,000 a year in funding to take innovative action to address these issues in their community.</p><p>Brilliant, innovative projects are already taking place across the country, and we will look closely at what has worked in Leeds, and with our Trailblazer councils to consider what more the Government can do to enable ambitious local action.</p>","South Ribble","Seema Kennedy",,"2019-05-08T13:55:26.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124237/answer","Biography information for Seema Kennedy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124237/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-05-01","Obesity: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he plans to take to promote the child-obesity strategy developed by Leeds City Council to improve levels of nutrition among children from disadvantaged households in other areas of the UK.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","249880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124238","Treasury","false","2019-05-08","<p>Since 2015, 13 cases have been referred to the General Anti-Abuse Rule (GAAR) Advisory Panel. GAAR Advisory Panel opinions are published on GOV.UK.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-05-08T15:25:59.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124238/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124238/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-05-01","General Anti-abuse Rule Advisory Panel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many cases have been referred to the GAAR Advisory Panel since 2015.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","249975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124239","Treasury","false","2019-05-08","<p>HMRC does not record data on penalties related to offshore activities in a single system, as cases can be complex and involve a combination of offshore and onshore elements. The information requested is not available.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-05-08T15:23:57.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124239/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124239/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-05-01","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many penalties related to off-shore activities HMRC collected in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","249976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124240","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-05-08","<p>The Future Telecoms Infrastructure Review in July 2018 set out the Government’s strategy for delivering 5G ambitions. The ambitions on 5G are for the UK to become a world leader in the technology and for the majority of the population to have access to a 5G signal by 2027.</p><p> </p><p>The terms of reference for the Telecoms Supply Chain Review were published on gov.uk on 8 November 2018. The decisions of the Review will be announced in due course and to Parliament.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","249979","2019-05-08T10:22:09.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124240/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124240/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-05-01","5G","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether his Department has carried out an impact assessment on the effect of banning Huawei equipment from non-core components of the 5G network on the speed of 5G rollout.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","249977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124241","Treasury","false","2019-05-08","<p>HMRC does not record data on penalties paid by size of business so the information requested is not readily available and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-05-08T15:28:18.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124241/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124241/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-05-01","Taxation: Self-assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many late filing penalties HMRC collected in 2018 from small and medium-sized businesses.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","249978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124242","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-05-08","<p>The Future Telecoms Infrastructure Review in July 2018 set out the Government’s strategy for delivering 5G ambitions. The ambitions on 5G are for the UK to become a world leader in the technology and for the majority of the population to have access to a 5G signal by 2027.</p><p> </p><p>The terms of reference for the Telecoms Supply Chain Review were published on gov.uk on 8 November 2018. The decisions of the Review will be announced in due course and to Parliament.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","249977","2019-05-08T10:22:09.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124242/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124242/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-05-01","5G","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether the Government plans to change its 5G roll-out targets in light of the reported decision to limit the use of Huawei equipment in the UK's 5G infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","249979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124243","Cabinet Office","false","2019-05-08","<p>Information on the nationality of suppliers is not routinely held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Statistics on cross-border public procurement between EU Member States are collated and published periodically by the European Commission. The latest report is available at <a href="https://publications.europa.eu/en/publication-detail/-/publication/5c148423-39e2-11e7-a08e-01aa75ed71a1" target="_blank">https://publications.europa.eu/en/publication-detail/-/publication/5c148423-39e2-11e7-a08e-01aa75ed71a1</a></p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-05-08T14:20:48.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124243/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124243/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-05-01","Public Sector: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many public procurement contracts were awarded to foreign companies in 2018.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","249980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124244","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=249942" target="_blank">249942</a>.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","249983","2019-05-10T15:05:21.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124244/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124244/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Universal Credit: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what provisions are being made for severe disability premium (SDP) claimants who were moved on to universal credit before the transitional SDP amount came into force.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","249981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124245","Department for Transport","false","2019-05-13","<p>The Department monitors all Train Operating Companies closely to ensure delivery of services for passengers, and is in regular discussions with all Train Operators as part of its normal business.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-05-13T14:36:06.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124245/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124245/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-05-01","Railways: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions the Department for Transport's Operator of the last Resort has had with existing rail franchise operators on potential changes of ownership of those franchises.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","249982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124246","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer to Question <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=249942" target="_blank">249942</a>.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","249981","2019-05-10T15:05:21.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124246/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124246/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Severe Disability Premium","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the timescale is for her Department (a) to identify all claimants who are eligible for a transitional severe disability premium and (b) when that payment will be awarded to eligible claimants.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","249983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124247","Cabinet Office","false","2019-05-08","<p>Information on the nationality of suppliers for infrastructure contracts is not routinely held<br>centrally</p><p>Statistics on cross-border public procurement between EU Member States are collated and<br>published periodically by the European Commission. The latest report is available at<br>https://publications.europa.eu/en/publication-detail/-/publication/5c148423-39e2-11e7-a08e-<br>01aa75ed71a1</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-05-08T14:22:21.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124247/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124247/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-05-01","Public Sector: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many public infrastructure contracts were awarded to foreign companies in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","249984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124248","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-07","<p>This question has been interpreted as referring to actions taken by the Child Maintenance Service. The Department does hold information regarding:</p><ol><li>deductions from the benefits received by a paying parent on the Child Maintenance Service in order to pay Child Maintenance;</li><li>instances in which the details of non-compliant paying parents on the Child Maintenance Service have been shared with credit reference agencies.</li></ol><p>The Department has no immediate plans to publish this information. However, with the completion of the Child Support Agency case closure programme, and the implementation of the new Child Maintenance compliance and arrears strategy, the Department continues to review what information is included in regular publications.</p>","Colchester","Will Quince",,"2019-05-07T15:39:15.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124248/answer","Biography information for Will Quince","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124248/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether her Department plans to collect and publish (a) the number of deductions from benefits and (b) instances of sharing non-compliant parents' information with credit reference agencies.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","249881"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124249","Department for Transport","false","2019-05-13","<p>The Department does not comment on a live competition. All bids received for any franchise competition are evaluated against the requirements and instructions set out in the relevant Invitation To Tender.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2019-05-13T14:27:16.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124249/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124249/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-05-01","West Coast Partnership Rail Franchise: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether First Group has met his Department's criteria on railway pensions as a shortlisted bidder for the West Coast Partnership rail franchise.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","249985"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124250","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-08","<p>There are many reasons people use foodbanks and agreement that growth in the use of foodbanks cannot be attributed solely to Universal Credit.</p><p>Under Universal Credit no claimant has to wait for their money: advances of up to 100 per cent of their award are available to all claimants from day one of their claim. Advances are paid back over a period of 12 months and in the Autumn Budget 2018, we announced that from October 2021, the payback period for these advances will be extended further, up to 16 months. This is just one of a number of measures the Department has put in place to support claimants, such as paying those claimants moving from Housing Benefit onto Universal Credit a two week ‘transitional housing payment’. We are also introducing a two-week run on for eligible claimants of Income Support, Jobseeker’s Allowance and Employment and Support Allowance from July 2020.</p>","Colchester","Will Quince",,"2019-05-08T14:11:25.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124250/answer","Biography information for Will Quince","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124250/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Universal Credit: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment her Department has made of a potential link between the rollout of universal credit and use of foodbanks in (a) Wales and (b) Ogmore.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","249986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124251","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-10","<p>The Government does not collect official data on the use of food banks. We have worked with the Scottish Government, food insecurity experts, and the Office for National Statistics to introduce a new set of food security questions in the Family Resources Survey starting from April 2019. This means that we will in future be able to able to monitor the prevalence and severity of household food insecurity across the UK and for specific groups, to better understand the drivers of food insecurity and identify which groups are most at risk.</p>","Colchester","Will Quince",,"2019-05-10T14:26:50.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124251/answer","Biography information for Will Quince","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124251/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Food Banks: Ogmore","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what data her Department collects on the use of food banks in Ogmore.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","249987"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124252","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-13","<p>Successive Governments have made decisions about the rates of benefits taking account of the competing demands on public expenditure, mindful of the need to balance poverty alleviation whilst not damaging incentives to work, as all Governments since 1948 have striven to do.</p><p> </p><p>Benefits provide a safety net for people to spend on their individual needs.</p><p>Government does not prescribe these, but provides support depending on circumstances such as ability to work and need for childcare.</p><p> </p><p>The applicable amount for Universal Credit is based upon a personal allowance paid according to age and family status, which can be supplemented by flat-rate premiums for groups recognised as having additional needs, such as disabled people and carers.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-05-13T16:22:01.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124252/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124252/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Universal Credit: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment she has made of whether universal credit adequately covers the cost of living in Wales.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","249988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124253","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-13","<p>The information requested is not held by the Department.</p><p> </p><p>Our latest published data shows that consistently around 85% of new claimants are being paid in full and on time. This can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/universal-credit-statistics</a>.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-05-13T12:28:02.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124253/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124253/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Universal Credit: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claimants received an underpayment of universal credit (a) as their first payment and (b) in further payments in (a) Ogmore and (b) Wales in 2018.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","249989"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124254","Cabinet Office","false","2019-05-08","<p>The Public Procurement Regulations require public sector buyers to pay their suppliers<br>within 30 days and require these payment terms to be passed down the supply chain</p><p>Where this is not happening, businesses are encouraged to raise this with the Public<br>Procurement Review Service, who will investigate. The Public Procurement Review Service<br>will also proactively ensure that 30-day payment terms are being passed down the supply<br>chain by carrying out spot checks on contracting authorities</p><p>From September, suppliers who do not pay their subcontractors on time may face exclusion<br>from winning government contracts.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2019-05-08T14:19:44.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124254/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124254/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-05-01","Public Sector: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what enforcement and review mechanisms are in place to ensure 30-day payment clauses are in place for suppliers and subcontractors contracted to work with private sector companies on outsourced public sector contracts.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","249990"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124255","Home Office","false","2019-05-08","<p>Stalking is an insidious crime that has a deep and significant impact on vic-tims’ wellbeing. Both online and offline, perpetrators leave victims feeling constantly at risk and looking over their shoulder. This Government is committed to ensuring that victims are supported.</p><p>Our National Statement of Expectations for Violence Against Women and Girls (VAWG), published in December 2016, sets out the standards which local commissioners should meet when putting in place services to respond to VAWG, including stalking. This includes the need to put the victim at the cen-tre of service delivery.</p><p>The Home Office part-funds the National Stalking Helpline, operated by the Suzy Lamplugh Trust, which has helped over 30,000 people since its inception. Through a grant of £4.1m under the Police Transformation Fund, the Government is also funding the Multi-Agency Stalking Intervention Programme. This aims, across three sites, to test and compare strategies to reduce recidivism on the part of stalking perpetrators and to develop best practice. This should improve the response to victims of stalking, ensuring that they receive consistently high-quality service and improving their satisfaction with police and across the criminal justice system.</p><p>The Stalking Protection Act 2019, which received Royal Assent on 15th March, will introduce Stalking Protection Orders. These will provide protection to victims at an early stage. Restraining orders can also be issued to those who have been prosecuted for stalking offences, to prevent continued stalking behaviour.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-05-08T16:49:28.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124255/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124255/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-05-01","Stalking: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps his Department is taking to support victims of stalking.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","249991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124256","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-05-08","<p>The number of people cautioned for stalking in each of the last five years can be found in the Outcomes by Offence data tool available here:</p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733981/outcomes-by-offence-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733981/outcomes-by-offence-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>Select 8.Q Stalking from the Offence drop down list</p><p> </p><p>Court proceedings and convictions data for 2018 are planned for publication on 16 May 2019</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar",,"2019-05-08T15:40:23.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124256/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124256/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-05-01","Stalking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have been cautioned for stalking in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","249992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124257","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-10","<p>We do not keep information on the number of times Financial Investigation Unit (FIU) request information from financial institutions to check the accuracy of information.</p><p> </p><p>Regarding the number of times Financial Investigation Unit (FIU) will seek to prosecute or forward to HMRC for fraud action. I can confirm there has been one prosecution in 2019 with 3 other cases are being investigated by Crown Prosecution Service. The arrangements with HMRC to provide them with information regarding Child Maintenance Group investigations has been finalised and the first transfer of data will occur in mid May.</p>","Colchester","Will Quince",,"2019-05-10T14:47:10.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124257/answer","Biography information for Will Quince","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124257/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 29 April 2019 to Question 246453, on Children: Maintenance, how many times each of the powers listed in the Answer have been used.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","249882"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124258","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-05-09","<p>The Resources and Waste Strategy sets out our ambition to eliminate avoidable waste. We welcome initiatives which keep waste out of landfill, such as reusable nappy schemes, whilst recognising the importance of wider environmental considerations such as energy usage. The Government is carrying out research on nappies that will look at such issues as the relative energy, water and waste impacts of the alternatives.</p><p> </p><p>We are exploring policy options in line with our commitment in the strategy and will develop proposals in due course for a range of individual products, including disposable hygiene products. This will involve in-depth discussions with industry and other stakeholders.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-05-09T15:21:59.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124258/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124258/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-05-01","Nappies: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what support the Government is providing for the introduction of reusable nappy schemes by local authorities.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","249993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124259","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-05-09","<p>HMCTS has published the value of ‘purchases of goods and services’ annually in its Annual Report and Accounts since it was formed on 1 April 2011.</p><p> </p><p>We are therefore only able to provide comparable data for HMCTS since its formation (along with the restated comparative figures from 2010-11). HMCTS’ purchases of goods and services are shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><p>2011-12</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-service-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2011-to-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-service-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2011-to-2012</a></p><p>2012-13</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2012-to-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2012-to-2013</a></p><p>2013-14</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014</a></p><p>2014-15</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015</a></p><p>2015-16</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</a></p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-05-09T17:08:44.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124259/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124259/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-05-01","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much Her Majesty's Courts and Tribunal Service spent on third-party suppliers in each financial year between 1 April 2008 and 31 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","249994"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124260","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-05-08","<p>Coroners are independent judicial office holders. As such it would not be appropriate for Ministers to comment on or seek to influence the conduct of their investigations.</p><p> </p><p>The Ministry of Justice does not hold information on the number of notices issued by coroners under schedule 5 to the Coroners and Justice Act 2009.</p><p> </p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar","249840","2019-05-08T15:22:13.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124260/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124260/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-05-01","Coroners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many notices were issued by coroners in England and Wales under Schedule 5 of the Coroners and Justice Act 2009 requiring the production of documents in each of the last three years for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Sir Christopher Chope","249839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124261","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-05-09","<p>HMCTS has published the value of consultant expenditure annually in its Annual Report and Accounts since it was formed on 1 April 2011.</p><p> </p><p>We are therefore only able to provide comparable data for HMCTS since its formation (along with the restated comparative figures from 2010-11).</p><p> </p><p>2011-12</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-service-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2011-to-2012" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-service-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2011-to-2012</a></p><p>2012-13</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2012-to-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2012-to-2013</a></p><p>2013-14</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014</a></p><p>2014-15</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-and-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2014-to-2015</a></p><p>2015-16</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2015-to-2016</a></p><p>2016-17</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hm-courts-tribunals-service-annual-report-and-accounts-2016-to-2017</a></p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-05-09T17:10:08.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124261/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124261/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-05-01","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much Her Majesty's Courts and Tribunal Service has spent from the public purse on consultancies in each financial year between 2008 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","249995"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124262","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-08","<p>Our Universal Credit Claimant Survey, found that 98 per cent of claimants have internet access and did claim online, and the majority of those said they found the claim process overall to be straightforward. This can be accessed at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-full-service-claimant-survey" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/universal-credit-full-service-claimant-survey</a></p><p>However, for those that are still unable to access or use digital services, assistance to make and maintain their claim is available via the Freephone Universal Credit helpline. Face-to-face support is also available in Jobcentres. In exceptional circumstances, a home visit can be arranged to support a claimant in making and maintaining their claim.</p><p>From 1 April 2019 Citizens Advice (England and Wales) and Citizens Advice Scotland are delivering the new ‘Help to Claim’ support to claimants making a new Universal Credit (UC) claim or moving from a legacy benefit to UC because of a change of circumstances. The Citizens Advice Help to Claim offers tailored, practical support to help people make a UC claim up to receiving their first full correct payment on time. It is available online, through web-chat, through a Freephone number and face to face through local Citizens Advice services.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-05-08T17:09:36.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124262/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124262/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that people who are digitally excluded are not missing out on benefits to which they are entitled.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","249804"
