"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124368","Treasury","false","2019-05-09","<p>The number of people loaned to each of these two departments in the last three years can be found in the following table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Department</p></td><td><p>April 2016 to March 2017</p></td><td><p>April 2017 to March 2018</p></td><td><p>April 2018 to March 2019</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DExEU</p></td><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DIT</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-05-09T15:08:09.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124368/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124368/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-05-01","Treasury: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249900"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124369","Cabinet Office","false","2019-05-09","<p>The number of civil servants seconded/loaned to a) the Department for Exiting the European Union from my Department in each of the last three years is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>2018</p></td><td><p>2019 to date</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>51</p></td><td><p>34</p></td><td><p>43</p></td><td><p>27</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>No civil servants were seconded/loaned to b) the Department for International Trade from my Department in any of the last three years.</p><p> </p><p>EU Exit is an all-of-government operation. DExEU, who share the Cabinet Office HR system, do not employ permanent staff. All civil service staff are loaned from other Government Departments or on fixed-term contracts. The Department for Exiting the European Union is responsible for overseeing negotiations to leave the EU and establishing the future relationship between the UK and EU. The Department for International trade works to secure UK and global prosperity by promoting and financing international trade and investment, and championing free trade.</p><p> </p><p>Departments continually review workforce plans, reprioritise and assess changing needs, which includes identification and cessation of non-priority work where appropriate. We have accelerated our plans, and at the same time, the Civil Service as a whole is working to ensure that EU Exit Implementation is carried out to high quality without impacting public service delivery across the whole of government.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2019-05-09T09:44:26.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124369/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124369/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-05-01","Cabinet Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to a) DexEU, and b) DiT in each of the last 3 years","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124370","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-05-07","<p>BEIS does not hold centrally the records of every Department loaned staff have joined. However, according to reports from BEIS’ two Shared Services providers during this period, the total number of BEIS staff loaned out in each year is as follows:</p><p>2016 – 47</p><p>2017 – 53</p><p>2018 – 48</p><p>2019 – 27</p><p>This data only reflects the loans fully recorded on Shared Services and so may not reflect all loans out of the Department.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson",,"2019-05-07T15:26:13.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124370/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124370/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-05-01","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249902"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124371","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-05-13","<p>In the Civil Service, a ‘secondment’ is a transfer to an external organisation, whereas the movement of staff to another Government department is usually referred to as a loan. We do not hold information centrally on the host departments of all secondees/loans from our department. However, we do hold a record of some employees on loan for whom we had to retrieve salary costs over the last 3 years:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Department for Exiting the European Union</p></td><td><p>Department for International Trade</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2019 (to present)</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2019-05-13T11:47:32.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124371/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124371/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-05-01","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124372","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-05-10","<p>This information can only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Work and Pension has worked closely with the Department for Exiting the European Union and other Government Departments as part of the UK’s preparations to exit the EU. The Department has prepared for all eventualities including no deal. Preparations have been undertaken by staff as part of their regular duties.</p>","Colchester","Will Quince",,"2019-05-10T14:18:22.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124372/answer","Biography information for Will Quince","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124372/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124372/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-05-01","Department for Work and Pensions: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many civil servants in her Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124373","Department for Education","false","2019-05-10","<p>The Civil Service is focused on delivering the government’s most pressing priorities, and this includes departments sharing staff and working together on joint projects.</p><p>Since January 2019, the department has been part of a coordinated resourcing exercise across the Civil Service to support preparations for leaving the EU without a deal. As part of this exercise, the department seconded 2 people to the Department for Exiting the European Union and 1 person to the Department for International Trade.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2019-05-10T09:13:51.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124373/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124373/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124373/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-05-01","Department for Education: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124374","Department for International Development","false","2019-05-08","<p>The below table details the number of DFID staff who have been seconded to the Department for Exiting the European Union and the Department for International Trade in each of the last three financial years.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>OGD</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017/18</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2018/19</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DEXEU</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>DIT</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>26</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>7</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>6</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>54</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2019-05-08T15:37:09.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124374/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124374/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-05-01","Department for International Development: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124375","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-05-13","<p>Between June 2016 and March 2018 a total of 11 civil servants have been loaned to the Department for Exiting the European Union and the Department for International Trade. These staff were loaned on two year contracts, some of which have already come to an end. All the outstanding DExEU loans are due to end in 2018/19, with the DIT loans due to end in 2020/21.</p><p> </p><p>Civil servants are loaned between other Government departments rather than seconded.</p><p> </p><p>Both departments were only formed in July 2016, therefore there is no data prior to this date.</p><p> </p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2019-05-13T16:57:12.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124375/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124375/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124375/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-05-01","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124376","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-05-08","<p>There have been no civil servants seconded from the Northern Ireland Office to either the Department for Exiting the European Union or the Department for International Trade, in each of the last three years.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2019-05-08T11:57:49.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124376/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124376/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-05-01","Northern Ireland Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many civil servants in her Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124377","Department for Transport","false","2019-05-08","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>The information requested for all three years can only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>However, of the information that is more readily available, the Central Department and its Executive Agencies does hold information for the previous year which is as follows:</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Department for Exiting the European Union (DExEU)</p></td><td><p>Department for International Trade (DIT)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2018 – 31 March 2019</p></td><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>5 or fewer</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-05-08T16:04:57.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124377/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124377/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-05-01","Department for Transport: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124378","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-05-09","<p>Overall, there have been four secondments to the Department for International Trade and 11 to the Department for Exiting the European Union. A full break down by year for the past three years is below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Department for International Trade</p></td><td><p>Department for Exiting the European Union</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2019</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-05-09T13:56:28.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124378/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124378/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124378/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-05-01","Department of Health and Social Care: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124379","Home Office","false","2019-05-13","<p>Please see the table below for the current numbers of civil servants that have temporarily moved out of the department to take up posts at DIT or DExEU in each of the last 3 years. The information provided is a list of current/active transfers that commenced in each of the three years. It is not possible to provide total numbers across the time period as the data on those that transferred out of the department but have since returned is not available.</p><table><tbody><tr><td>Year</td><td>Department for Exiting the European Union</td><td>Department for International Trade</td></tr><tr><td>2018/19</td><td>9</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td>2017/18</td><td>4</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>2016/17</td><td>1</td><td>1</td></tr><tr><td>Total</td><td>14</td><td>12</td></tr></tbody></table>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-05-13T16:01:55.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124379/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1124379/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-05-01","Home Office: Secondment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many civil servants in his Department have been seconded to (a) the Department for Exiting the European Union and (b) the Department for International Trade in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","249911"
